## Steps to Reproduce

1. Enable Flutter plugin v40.0.2
2. Update Android Studio to 3.5.1
3. Open plain Android Project
4. Run Gradle sync
5. it fails without error and in idea.log there is crash (below)
6. Disable Flutter plugin
7. Project syncs correctly

comment_data.body: Same thing happened to me also. Uninstalled dart and flutter plugin yesterday and it worked. But today although the plugins are removed I sometimes get the exception. Seems weird.

I cannot reproduce this problem.

I update Android Studio to 3.5.1 and have Flutter plugin 40.0.2 installed.

There is a lot of variability in Linux installations. If it isn't too much trouble you might try re-installing Android Studio from scratch -- it looks like you've been updating the same installation since 3.0. That should be ok, but it is the first thing I'd try. The NoClassDefFoundError specifies a class defined by Android Studio that wasn't present in 3.4 and earlier but was included in 3.5 IIRC.
I have reinstalled AS from scratch and the same error appears.

@dbacinski Thanks for trying. I was wrong about the history of the missing class. It has been part of the Gradle plugin since 2011. The Flutter plugin only started to rely on it in version 40. So you could get around this problem by dropping back to version 39. We'll look into it.

@dbacinski This looks like a classpath issue. The `NoClassDefFoundError` shouldn't happen because the class should be distributed with Android Studio.

Can you confirm that your Android Studio contains this file:
> C:\Program Files\Android\Android Studio\plugins\gradle\lib\gradle-common.jar

If you can, make a copy of that file, change the extension from "jar" to "zip" then check that it contains this file:
> org\jetbrains\plugins\gradle\util\GradleConstants.class

If the class is where it should be then the other possibility is that there is another gradle-common.jar on your classpath that does not have GradleConstants.

You are right, the correct jar is there.

![Screenshot from 2019-10-29 09-43-29](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/454414/67751083-c01cd500-fa30-11e9-8d72-1921f91457b7.png)

The only error in IDE while executing Gradle Sync is this:

![Screenshot from 2019-10-29 09-57-10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/454414/67752063-91076300-fa32-11e9-8b49-938ec8b72f19.png)


Can't find anything related in the logs apart from exception :/
